The paper discusses the performance limits of network densification in the context of cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also incorporates concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM) to develop a general framework for analyzing the performance of ultra-dense networks. Additionally, the paper discusses the scaling of network performance, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM).
